Class ReporterSettingsDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.jface.window.Window

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.jface.window.IShellProvider

    public class ReporterSettingsDialog
extends org.eclipse.jface.dialogs.Dialog
    Displays a Dialog that allows the user to set prefferences for the report generator. The prefferences are saved in the project directory as .reporterSettings. If it exists the file is loaded before the frame is displayed.
    Author:
    Joe Seibel

    • Constructor Detail

      • ReporterSettingsDialog

        public ReporterSettingsDialog(org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Shell parent,
                      org.eclipse.core.resources.IProject affectedProject)
        Creates and displays a new ReporterSettingsDialog. If a .reporterSettings is already assosiated with the IProject affectedProject, the settings file is loaded before the frame is displayed. When the user clicks on the frame's ok button, the settings will be saved to .reporterSettings within affectedProject.
        Parameters:
        affectedProject - .reporterSettings will be saved and loaded from this project.
